{"type":"message","id":"81a89437","parentId":"04d2c9aa","timestamp":"2026-04-17T15:51:00.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kNYwR8jrvhSXglBw2dXTPI0O|fc_01e0109cecb4ff730169e256d55a8081978bbce3214d0c6f7d","name":"edit","arguments":{"edits":[{"newText":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `GLOBAL.md` — this is the global, high-hit-rate rule layer\n3. Read `PERSONAL.md` — this is the user's long-term preference layer\n4. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n5. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n6. Read relevant `projects/*.md` only when the current task clearly matches that project\n7. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Instruction Layers\n\nKeep long-term instructions split across three layers so a single giant file does not dilute instruction hit rate:\n\n- `GLOBAL.md` — cross-task, stable, high-frequency rules\n- `PERSONAL.md` — user-specific long-term preferences and working style\n- `projects/*.md` — project or workflow specific rules, loaded only when relevant\n\nSee `INSTRUCTION_LAYERS.md` for migration and placement rules.\n\n## Memory\n","oldText":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\n\n## First Run\n\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\n\n## Session Startup\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\n\n## Memory\n"},{"newText":"### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- Keep `MEMORY.md` curated and compact. Do not turn it into a second giant instruction file.\n- Long-term user preferences belong in `PERSONAL.md`; project rules belong in `projects/*.md`\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n","oldText":"### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\n\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\n"}],"path":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/AGENTS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"edits\":[{\"newText\":\"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\\n\\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\\n\\n## First Run\\n\\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\\n\\n## Session Startup\\n\\nBefore doing anything else:\\n\\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\\n2. Read `GLOBAL.md` — this is the global, high-hit-rate rule layer\\n3. Read `PERSONAL.md` — this is the user's long-term preference layer\\n4. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\\n5. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\\n6. Read relevant `projects/*.md` only when the current task clearly matches that project\\n7. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\\n\\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\\n\\n## Instruction Layers\\n\\nKeep long-term instructions split across three layers so a single giant file does not dilute instruction hit rate:\\n\\n- `GLOBAL.md` — cross-task, stable, high-frequency rules\\n- `PERSONAL.md` — user-specific long-term preferences and working style\\n- `projects/*.md` — project or workflow specific rules, loaded only when relevant\\n\\nSee `INSTRUCTION_LAYERS.md` for migration and placement rules.\\n\\n## Memory\\n\",\"oldText\":\"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\\n\\nThis folder is home. Treat it that way.\\n\\n## First Run\\n\\nIf `BOOTSTRAP.md` exists, that's your birth certificate. Follow it, figure out who you are, then delete it. You won't need it again.\\n\\n## Session Startup\\n\\nBefore doing anything else:\\n\\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\\n\\nDon't ask permission. Just do it.\\n\\n## Memory\\n\"},{\"newText\":\"### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\\n\\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\\n- Keep `MEMORY.md` curated and compact. Do not turn it into a second giant instruction file.\\n- Long-term user preferences belong in `PERSONAL.md`; project rules belong in `projects/*.md`\\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\\n\",\"oldText\":\"### 🧠 MEMORY.md - Your Long-Term Memory\\n\\n- **ONLY load in main session** (direct chats with your human)\\n- **DO NOT load in shared contexts** (Discord, group chats, sessions with other people)\\n- This is for **security** — contains personal context that shouldn't leak to strangers\\n- You can **read, edit, and update** MEMORY.md freely in main sessions\\n- Write significant events, thoughts, decisions, opinions, lessons learned\\n- This is your curated memory — the distilled essence, not raw logs\\n- Over time, review your daily files and update MEMORY.md with what's worth keeping\\n\"}],\"path\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/AGENTS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":42616,"output":828,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":43444,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776441040784,"responseId":"resp_01e0109cecb4ff730169e256d211888197a769afe6b91155b0"}}
